The winged deity forsook their view, And in a moment to Olympus flew.
Now shed Aurora round her saffron ray, Sprung through the gates of light, and gave the day.
Charg d with their mournful load to Ilion go
The sage and king, majestically slow.
Cassandra first beholds, from Ilion's spire, The sad procession of her hoary sire ;
Then, as the pensive pomp advanc'd more near, (Her breathless brother stretch'd upon the bier,) A shower of tears o'erflows her beauteous eyes, Alarming thus all Ilion with her cries:
